.TH WSD\-DISCOVER 1 "2026-04-15" "truenas-pydiscovery" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wsd\-discover \- discover WSD devices on the local network
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wsd\-discover
.RB [ \-t
.IR TIMEOUT ]
.RB [ \-r ]
.RB [ \-i
.IR ADDR ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wsd\-discover
sends a WS\-Discovery Probe via UDP multicast and lists all
responding devices with their endpoint references and metadata
endpoint URLs (XAddrs).
.PP
No daemon is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-t " TIMEOUT" "\fR,\fP \-\-timeout " TIMEOUT
Discovery timeout in seconds.
Default: 4.0.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-resolve
Fetch metadata (FriendlyName, Computer, Manufacturer) for each
discovered device via HTTP.
When a ProbeMatch omits XAddrs \(em Windows hosts do this by
default for privacy \(em a unicast WS\-Discovery Resolve is sent to
extract the transport URL before the HTTP Get.
.TP
.BI \-i " ADDR" "\fR,\fP \-\-interface " ADDR
Interface IPv4 address to send from.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSONL (one JSON object per discovered device).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
wsd\-discover
wsd\-discover \-\-resolve \-\-json
wsd\-discover \-t 10 \-i 192.168.1.100
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wsd\-info (1),
.BR truenas\-wsd (8)
